  "text": "for any X, Y ∈ Γ(T M ) and any ψ, ϕ ∈ Γ(ΣM ). The usual Dirac operator ∂ / is defined by ∂ / ψ := γ α · ∇ γα ψ for a local orthonormal frame {γ α } m α=1 on M and a usual spinor ψ ∈ Γ(ΣM ). The summation convention will be used throughout the paper. We refer to [24, [CITATION_1] ",
